<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--ChristiansSentenced     04-18 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Christians Sentenced,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thirteen Jailed For Converting To Christianity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge convicted and sentenced 13 men to
eight months in prison for converting to Christianity, the Nepalese
news agency RSS reported.
   Judge Nav Raj Upadhyaya of the Makwanpur District Court in
Bhimphedi, 30 miles south of the capital, on Sunday handed down the
sentences of eight months and 15 days to each of the men, RSS
reported Monday.
   Police arrested the 13 on August 10 and charged them with
changing their religion.
   Christian missions are permitted in Nepal, but conversion is
forbidden. Ninety percent of the country's 16 million people are
Hindu, Buddhists comprise 5 percent and Moslems 3 percent.
</TEXT>
