<HEAD>Princess Nori Turns 20, Becomes Adult Member Of Imperial Family</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Princess Nori, the only daughter of Emperor Akihito
and Empress Michiko, turned 20 today and officially became an adult
member of the imperial family, palace officials said.
   No birthday celebration was planned at the palace for the
princess because the imperial family is observing a one-year period
of mourning for the late Emperor Hirohito, said a palace official
on condition of anonymity.
   Hirohito died Jan. 7 at the age of 87.
   The princess, a sophomore majoring in Japanese literature at
Gakushuin University in Tokyo, is expected to appear more often at
public events now that she can be present at gatherings minors are
not permitted to attend, he said.
