<FIRST>r w BC-HouseEthics-Thumbnails     04-18 0662</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-House Ethics-Thumbnails,660</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are thumbnail sketches of the 12 members
of the House ethics committee and the investigator who prepared
Monday's report charging House Speaker Jim Wright with violating
the rules of conduct:
   Rep. Julian C. Dixon, 54, chairman of the Committee on Standards
of Official Conduct ... Democrat from Culver City, Calif. ... first
elected to Congress in 1978 ... attorney and former California
assemblyman ... former chairman of the Congressional Black Caucus
... member of the Appropriations Committee and chairman of its
subcommittee on the District of Columbia.
   Rep. John T. Myers, 62, the ranking Republican on the ethics
panel ... from Covington, Ind. ... first elected to Congress in
1966 ... owns and operates a grain and livestock farm ... onetime
cashier and officer with the Fountain Trust Co. in Covington ...
third-ranking Republican on the Appropriations Committee.
   Rep. Hank Brown, 49, Republican from Greeley, Colo. ...
president of the large Republican class elected to the House in
1980 ... lawyer and Vietnam veteran ... considered a prime
contender for the GOP nomination for the seat that Sen. William L.
Armstrong will vacate next year ... member of Ways and Means
Committee.
   Rep. Larry E. Craig, 43, Republican from Boise, Idaho ... like
Brown, a member of the House class of 1980 ... a former
farmer-rancher and member of the Idaho Senate ... also serves on
the Public Works and Transportation and Interior committees.
   Rep. Thomas E. Petri, 48, Republican from Fond du Lac, Wis. ...
first elected in April 1979 to fill the vacancy left by death of
Republican William Steiger ... Harvard-trained lawyer and former
Peace Corps volunteer ... sits on the Education and Labor, and
Public Works committees.
   Rep. Charles Pashayan Jr., 48, Republican from Fresno, Calif.
... lawyer who worked at the Department of Health, Education and
Welfare under Elliot Richardson in the early 1970s ... staunch
conservative ... known as Chip, he unseated a Democratic incumbent
in 1978 ... ranking Republican on the Interior subcommittee on
water, a key concern in his agricultural district.
   Rep. James V. Hansen, 56, Republican from Salt Lake City, Utah
... former speaker of the Utah House ... worked in real estate and
insurance business ... Navy veteran who served in Korea ... sits on
the Armed Services and Interior committees.
   Rep. Chester G. Atkins, 41, Democrat from Concord, Mass. ...
spent 14 years in the Massachusetts House and Senate before winning
his seat in Congress in 1984 ... born in Geneva, Switzerland ...
also serves on the Appropriations Committee.
   Rep. Joseph M. Gaydos, 52, Democrat from McKeesport, Pa. ...
serving 11th term in Congress ... former Pennsylvania state
senator, deputy attorney general ... also was attorney for the
United Mine Workers of America District 5 ... labor stalwart and
chairman of the Education and Labor subcommittee on health and
safety.
   Rep. Alan B. Mollohan, 45, Democrat from Fairmont, W.Va. ...
lawyer serving his fourth term in Congress ... won the seat his
father previously held ... serves on the Appropriations Committee
... champion of steel and coal.
   Rep. Vic Fazio, 46, Democrat from West Sacramento, Calif. ... a
former California legislator and co-founder of California Journal
magazine ... won his House seat in 1978 ... respected as an
insider's insider, he chairs the Appropriations subcommittee on the
legislative branch.
   Rep. Bernard J. Dwyer, 68, Democrat from Edison, N.J. ... former
insurance executive ... rose to majority leader during a six-year
stint in the New Jersey Senate in the 1970s before being elected to
Congress in 1980 ... also sits on the Appropriations, Intelligence
and Budget committees.
   Richard J. Phelan, 52, special outside counsel to the ethics
panel ... Chicago lawyer active in Democratic politics ...
supported Sen. Paul Simon, D-Ill., in last year's presidential
primaries ... founding partner of Phelan, Pope &amp; John, a firm
specializing in civil litigation ... former president of the
Chicago Bar Association ... graduate of Georgetown Law School.
</TEXT>
