<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--MissingGavel     04-18 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Missing Gavel,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Missing Gavel Brings Laughs During Testy Debate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JEFFERSON CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. Danny Staples reached for his
gavel to bring his rowdy colleagues to order. But the gavel was
missing, so he went for the next best thing: the heel of his shoe.
   Staples was presiding over the Senate Monday night during a rare
evening session in which the chamber debated a dog-racing bill.
   When the chatter and noise got to be too much, Staples looked
for the gavel amd when he couldn't find it, he removed his shoe and
banged the heel on the lecturn.
   ``It's a night session and there's going to be order,'' Staples
said in explaining his decision.
   When other senators noticed the makeshift gavel, laughter broke
up the sometimes testy debate. They came to the rescue, finding a
replacement wooden gavel that Staples used the rest of the night.
   The bill was defeated.
</TEXT>
