<HEAD>Dollar Gains Against Yen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar gained against the Japanese yen in
trading in Tokyo on Tuesday, and stock prices recovered from an
early setback.
   The dollar closed at 132.10 yen, up 0.27 yen from Monday's
finish of 131.83 yen. The dollar opened higher at 132.23 yen and
ranged between 132.00 and 132.27 yen during the day.
   Traders said the dollar-yen exchange rate changed little as
participants avoided making any major moves ahead of the scheduled
release of the U.S. consumer price index for March later Tuesday.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues added another 13.33 points, or 0.04 percent, to
finish trading at 33,321.66, another record high. The stock average
gained 157.89 points on Monday.
   Dealers said the Nikkei index recovered after an initial decline
as participants began buying steel and machinery issues.
   Trading was active despite the coming release of U.S. consumer
prices, said a dealer with a major securities firm in Tokyo.
   Volume on the exchange's first section was estimated at 1.1
billion shares, up from 750 million shares on Monday.
