<SECOND>PM-Philippines-Rebels,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Guerrillas Attack Army Depot, Kill 6 Soldiers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 200 communist guerrillas firing
automatic weapons and grenade launchers attacked an army supply
depot in the central Philippines today and killed six soldiers, the
military reported.
   The raiders also wounded 10 soldiers and captured two others
during the 3{-hour firefight in the town of Candoni in Negros
Occidental province, about 350 miles southeast of Manila, an army
spokesman said.
   Negros Island, the country's sugar bowl, is considered a
stronghold of the communist New People's Army.
   The two captured soldiers were later abandoned in a house
several miles from the clash site, the official said.
   He quoted the two soldiers as saying at least 30 of the raiders
were killed, but the report could not be independently verified.
   ``They were carrying them aboard several bamboo carts drawn by
carabaos (water buffaloes) with bodies piled up, one on top of the
other,'' he added.
   The rebel army has been waging a 20-year-old war in a bid to
establish a Marxist state in the Philippines.
