<HEAD>Millionaire Actress And Singer Says She Still Has Working Class Values</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Madonna, 30 years old and rich, says she's just
a ``working-class girl'' in some respects.
   She told Vogue magazine in its May issue that she can be a bit
of a tightwad even though the money is there.
   ``I hate waste and I hate to waste money. I don't see the point
of having more than one car. And I hate to waste food,'' said
Madonna, who reportedly made $46 million in 1988.
   ``Well, there's a difference between being born into money and
making money. I've made my money. I'm from a poor background and
basically I'm still a working-class girl in terms of my ethics,''
she said.
   Madonna told the magazine that splitting up with actor Sean Penn
after three years of marriage hurts but has not left her depressed.
   ``Sad. I'm sad about it,'' she said. ``Very sad. You can't be
married to somebody for 3{ years and then just forget him.''
