<FILEID>AP-NR-04-18-89 0849EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-China-Quake     04-18 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-China-Quake,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>Seven Killed By Aftershocks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven people died today in the aftershocks of a
serious earthquake that struck a remote southwestern region, the
state-run news agency said.
   The initial tremor Sunday, measuring 6.7 on the Richter scale,
was centered on Batang county, a mountainous area near Sichuan
province's western border with Tibet. At least four were reported
killed.
   The official Xinhua News Agency said today's aftershocks killed
seven people, injured 37 and destroyed 700 houses. The strongest
aftershock measured 4.4 on the Richter scale, Xinhua said.
   Communications with Batang were hampered by heavy snow Sunday
and disrupted phone lines Monday, the agency said.
   It said casualties and damage in neighboring Markam county, a
region inhabited by Tibetans, were not known because roads to the
region were blocked. The Richter scale is a gauge of energy
released by an earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded
on a seismograph. A quake measuring 6 can cause severe damage in a
populated area.
</TEXT>
