04-18 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-France-Plane Purchase, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0527,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Irish Company Places Biggest Plane Order in History</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS thruout to CORRECT size of new order to 308 sted 819 and
lower cost of order; no pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GPA Group Ltd. today announced it was ordering 308
planes, the largest single purchase of aircraft in aviation history.
   The $16.8 billion order will be shared by the American companies
Boeing and McDonnell-Douglas, and Airbus, a European consortium,
officials of the Irish aircraft-leasing company said.
   A similar announcement was made in London today, and a news
conference was scheduled for New York as well.
   The biggest previous aviation order _ worth $10.5 billion _ was
placed by Delta Air Lines last September for 225 orders and options
on Boeing and McDonnell-Douglas airplanes.
   The current order combines with previous orders announced in
1986 to bring the total GPA buying program to 819 planes worth
about $30 billion. That figure includes some planes already
delivered.
