<SECOND>PM-Soviet-Flood,0112</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Rivers Overflow, Destroy 300 Houses In Uzbekistan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three rivers flooded their banks and a
cotton-growing region in Uzbekistan, destroying 300 homes and
submerging 300 more, Tass news agency reported today.
   More than 2,000 people were evacuated in time and no one was
killed when the flood hit the Andizhan region of the Central Asian
republic Monday evening, the Soviet agency said.
   The Mailisai, Tentaksai, and Chirtaksai rivers swelled because
of torrential rains, carrying away the seeds planted for thousands
of acres of cotton and other crops, Tass said.
   Residents are building dikes against the rivers' waters, which
remain high, it said.
