<FIRST>u i PM-Cuba-JetCrash     04-18 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Cuba-Jet Crash,0196</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cuban MiG-21 Crashes Into Homes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Cuban air force MiG-21 fighter jet crashed
into three houses today in the Cuban city of Holguin, the official
Cuban news agency Prensa Latina reported. There was no immediate
word on casualties.
   The agency quoted an airport official as saying the Soviet-made
fighter slammed into the homes at 9 a.m. in Holguin, about 470
miles east of the capital of Havana.
   The dispatch monitored in Mexico City did not say what caused
the crash.
   Firefighters blocked off the crash site while rescue workers and
military personnel searched for possible victims, the report said.
   ``Radio reporters in Holguin told Prensa Latina the plane,
belonging to the province's air base, completely destroyed a house
at 88 Jose A. Cardet St. and caused serious damages to at least two
others,'' the agency said.
   A witness said the fighter flew ``like it was riding a wave,
moving constantly at low altitude with its lights on'' seconds
before the crash, the report said.
   It said the plane went down in a working class residential
neighborhood several blocks from a public school.
</TEXT>
