<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Sen. John G. Tower has gone back to an old
job since he wasn't able to get a Senate OK to run the Defense
Department.
   The Texan, who was turned down for secretary of defense because
of allegations of drinking and womanizing, has been appointed to
the board of directors of New York publisher Macmillan Inc., its
parent company Maxwell Communication Corp. PLC said Tuesday.
   Tower used to be chairman of Pergamon-Brassey's Washington-based
International Defense Publications Inc. and of Pergamon-Brassey's
U.S. Armed Forces Journal. He now has resumed these posts, Maxwell
Communication said.
   Tower served as U.S. senator from 1961 to 1985. Among other
posts, he served as chairman of the Armed Services Committee.
