<TEXT>
   U.S. Rep. Claude Pepper, the oldest member of
Congress, is in Walter Reed Army Medical Center with stomach
problems.
   The 88-year-old Miami Democrat entered the hospital 12 days ago
complaining of vomiting and nausea, said aide Rochelle Jones, who
declined to comment on Pepper's health or when he may return to
work.
   The hospital referred all inquiries Monday back to Pepper's
office.
   ``They have not absolutely ruled out some sort of parasite, but
they are now under the belief that it's a virus and are treating
him for it,'' said Fran Campbell in the senator's office.
