<HEAD>Suspected Former Mafia Boss Slain in Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 80-year-old reputed former Mafia boss
was shot to death Tuesday as he drove his car outside Palermo,
police said.
   Antonino Mineo was a top Mafia figure in the 1960s, according to
Tommaso Buscetta, a former mob member turned informer whose 1986
testimony led to the trial of hundreds of alleged Mafia members.
Mineo was acquitted in 1987 for lack of sufficient evidence.
   Investigators told the AGI news agency that the slaying near
Bagheria was probably linked to Mafia killings in the area in
recent days.
   Police said Mineo appeared to have been shot by two gunmen. No
witnesses came forward, the ANSA news agency said.
   According to Buscetta, Mineo was stripped of his Mafia
leadership in the mid-1970s because of his age.
