<HEAD>Five Dead In Shootout Between Anti-Drug Agents, Traffickers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GUATEMALA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anti-drug investigators and alleged drug
traffickers exchanged gunfire at the University of San Carlos
campus, and two agents and three suspects were killed, the
government announced Tuesday.
   Details about how the shootout Monday began were unclear.
   Carlos Chen, police spokesman, said the drug suspects opened
fire on the police agents, who chased them to a nearby ravine in
the southern part of the capital.
   He said one agent and one alleged trafficker were found dead at
the campus and other bodies were found in the ravine. The second
police agent died in the hospital.
   The government said that drug traffickers have been operating at
the university, which is independent.
   Chen identified the dead agents as Humberto Leonardo Cifuentes,
32, and German Carranza Monzon, 28. Another agent, Hector Humberto
Gomez, was wounded.
