<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--TanzaniaFloods     04-18 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Tanzania Floods,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Heavy Rain, Floods Cause Damage in Tanzania</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAR ES SALAAM, Tanzania (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rains and floods have
stranded tens of thousands of people, left hundreds more homeless
and cut highways and railroad lines in Tanzania, the state news
agency reported Tuesday.
   The agency said more than 43,000 people were trapped in 12
villages in southern Tanzania after more than two weeks of heavy
rains washed out roads and bridges in Kyela District.
   More than 1,000 people were left homeless in the town of
Morogoro, in central Tanzania, after flash floods caused by a heavy
downpour washed away their houses last weekend, the agency said.
   Tanzania Railways Corp. was forced to close its Mpanda branch
line because water was flowing about 2{ feet above the rail level
and still rising, the agency said.
