<FIRST>r i AM-BRF---ParkingTickets     04-18 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF---Parking Tickets,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Egypt Leads Diplomatic Missions in Ignoring Parking Tickets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Egypt led London's diplomatic missions in refusing
to pay parking tickets for its vehicles oin 1988, beating the
Soviet Union by a narrow margin, according to figures released
Tuesday by the Foreign Office.
   Egypt topped the list for the second year, according to the
report, claiming diplomatic immunity and ignoring 668 parking
tickets in 1988 compared to 799 in 1987.
   It said Moscow's envoys ignored 656 tickets last year and 622 in
1987.
   A Foreign Office official, Tim Eggar, said the total last year
for all diplomatic missions was 10,079.
