jetliner returned safely to Miami International Airport,
authorities said.
   No bomb was found aboard the plane, police said.
   About half an hour after Flight 975 departed for San Juan, the
suspect indicated he was in possession of a bomb, and the pilot
directed the plane back to Miami, said FBI spokesman Paul Miller.
   The A-300 Airbus carrying 205 passengers and a crew of nine
landed safely in Miami at about 2:50 p.m., and the passengers used
chutes to quickly evacuate on a remote section of the field, Miller
said.
   Two passengers suffered minor injuries coming down the chute,
Miller said. They were treated at a local hospital and released.
   Armando Rosado, 21, of Ponce, Puerto Rico, was arrested and
charged with interference with flight crew members and false
information and threats, Miller said.
