measured by the Consumer Price Index, jumped 0.5 percent in March,
fueled by higher costs for food and energy. That followed rises of
0.6 percent in January and 0.4 percent in February and put the
annual inflation rate at 6.1 percent, higher than the 4.4 percent
increase in 1988.
