<FIRST>r f BC-HolidayInn     04-18 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Holiday Inn,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Holiday Inn Adds 14 Hotels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two hotels in China are among six new and
eight converted hotels added to the Holiday Inn chain in the first
quarter of 1989, the chain's parent company announced Tuesday.
   The two hotels in the People's Republic of China, in Xian and
Chongging, give the company a total of five hotels in China,
Holiday Corp. said. Two more hotels are scheduled to open later
this year in Guangzhou and Dalian. Holiday Corp. expects to operate
a total of 20 hotels in China by 1995.
   The remaining four new hotels opened in Columbus, Ohio; Lima,
Ohio; Decatur, Ga.; and Cancun, Mexico.
   Of the eight hotels converted to Holiday Inns, six are in the
United States, one in Ratigen, Germany, and one in Leige, Belgium.
   Holiday Inn plans to add 50 hotels in 1989, with more than half
of those converted hotels. The chain is the world's largest hotel
operator, with 1,590 hotels in 51 countries.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
